in in other dungeons. And whatever you say, the problem is each time the levels are increased, the low levels are left out. Would would get some fun raiding Befallen at leve 15, Unrest ... Lguk and some others ... and as soon as you try to kill higher stuff, you see 2 levels 60 sitting there, and farming them. You could try to kill VS, you should have to be happy that a wizard with MB and 3 friends didn't come down to farm it. So you can imagine a group of level 65 farming planes. I personnaly see Verant politics as a perfectly known suicide. They are making people waiting a little longer to reset the game with Everquest II. Cause for all people that can't play few hours a day and finally reach high level, they can't do high end stuff, cause they don't play enough. So they will continue buffing newbies. And I consider that all low-mid level guilds will disappear with PoP. Or will remain only the ones that accept to be &quot;step stones&quot;.<br>
One thing that should have been done: increase low level dungeons loots with a system of mirors (like in ToFS) but with a level limit to go through them. That would give so much fun for low levels. But Verant considers only high level people (just see for Mana burn, ok wizards are powerful at level 60+, but for all wizards that aren't there, it is a pain). Anyway, whatever we say, whatever we do, they will increase level caps, or at least AA, but that will be still the same thing.... just remember that people that made this game, now just want to get the most cash now, before introducing Eq II. They will be happy to reset the stuff of all players (the one that will decide to move), cause they are coming to a point that makes them giving 5 billions hp to a shroom to make it as if it was hard mobs. And swords with dmg 540 delay 5.... when I started Eq, the ultimate weapon was the Executionner's axe in Lguk. Today send a group of mains (understand: not alts) in Lguk and they finally loot it, I can already see: &quot;pass&quot; ... &quot;pass&quot; ... &quot;me too&quot; ... &quot;I'll take it, it worths 25pp to a mercant&quot; ... And that already starts being same thing with planes.... <br>
<br>
*goes back into his tavern*, at least beer is still cheap in the game...<br>
<br>
that's why I hacve accepted the fact I couldn't do high end stuff, cause I don't want to get into a guild where we talk only about epics, and high end mobs in guild chat. That's also why I prefer doing fun events with my guild such a naked unbuffed level 1 people race through dreadlands.For haviing done it, I can say that dodging level 35 mobs when you know you are level 1, gives lots of adrenaline. We also tried to go as far as we can in Karnor Castle with our level 1 people...and what made me really laugh is when I started attacking a mob a in the group that was on it, a guy told me: &quot;this place is camped, please don't KS or I'll petition&quot;. I guess this kind of people will be 65 one day lol.. I don't want to be with them. <p><center><img src="http://finalgrunt.free.fr/pics/gruntou.jpg"></center>
